      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can understand your frustration, but Sudafed contains pseudoephedrine, which I wouldn't recommend during pregnancy without consulting your doctor first. Your baby's safety is paramount, and while a small dose might seem harmless, it could still pose risks. It's better to stay awake with a warm cup of tea and rest on your side, which can help with both congestion and reduce the risk of preterm labor. Maybe try some peppermint tea, which can also soothe your sinuses. I would really urge you to call your doctor's after-hours number if you have one; they might be able to give you immediate advice or even prescribe a safe medication for you to use while pregnant.",
